java.util.EventListener, NamedObjectAPI, ParameterChangeListener
public class IMRGuiBean
extends java.lang.Object
implements NamedObjectAPI, ParameterChangeListener

Title: IMRGuiBean

Description: This class is a java bean container for all the Gui elements and controller elements for one particular IMR. This allows all the components to be packaged up in this one class and then for every IMR that is created there will be one instance of this bean. This allows these beans to be easily swapped in and out when you are examining different IMR's in the main tester applet application.

Constructor Detail

IMRGuiBean

public IMRGuiBean(java.lang.String className,
                  java.lang.String name,
                  IMRTesterApplet applet)
Constructor for the IMRGuiBean object. This constructor is passed in a IMR class name, a name for the Gui bean, and the main applet. From this info. the IMR class is created at run time along with the paramater change listener just by the name of the classes.Finally the paramater editors are created for the independent and control paramaters.
Parameters:
className - Fully qualified package and class name of the IMR class
name - Placeholder name for this Gui bean so it could be referenced in a hash table or hash map.
applet - The main applet application that will use these beans to swap in and out different IMR's.
Method Detail

createIMRClassInstance

public static java.lang.Object createIMRClassInstance(java.lang.String className,
                                                      ParameterChangeWarningListener listener)
Creates a class instance from a string of the full class name including packages. This is how you dynamically make objects at runtime if you don't know which\ class beforehand. For example, if you wanted to create a BJF_1997_IMR you can do it the normal way:

BJF_1997_IMR imr = new BJF_1997_IMR()

If your not sure the user wants this one or AS_1997_IMR you can use this function instead to create the same class by:

BJF_1997_IMR imr = (BJF_1997_IMR)ClassUtils.createNoArgConstructorClassInstance("org.scec.sha.imt.classicImpl.BJF_1997_IMR");

synchToModel

public void synchToModel()
Resets all GUI controls back to the model values. Some models have been changed when iterating over an independent variable. This function ensures these changes are reflected in the independent parameter list.

parameterChange

public void parameterChange(ParameterChangeEvent event)
This is the main function of this interface. Any time a control paramater or independent paramater is changed by the user in a GUI this function is called, and a paramater change event is passed in. This function then determines what to do with the information ie. show some paramaters, set some as invisible, basically control the paramater lists.

initIndependentParamListAndEditor

private void initIndependentParamListAndEditor(IMRTesterApplet applet)
                                        throws ParameterException
This function gets the independent paramaters lists from the IMR and then creates the list editor. These editors know what type of Gui element to present in the list based on the data type of each paramater. There is a default location where it looks for these editor classes if it cannot be found there it will look in the special editors package file path.
